                <h1>What is a Bodega? Your Essential Guide</h1>
                <p>A bodega is a small grocery store or convenience shop, often found in urban areas, particularly in Latino neighborhoods. These shops offer a wide range of products, including groceries, snacks, and household items, often operating long hours to serve the community. They are hubs for local culture, providing a sense of familiarity and convenience.</p>
